Welcome to April's Turing-Roche newsletter! Here you can find what's new in the Turing-Roche strategic partnership and opportunities, events and news from both The Alan Turing Institute and Roche.

Our [five year partnership](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FfG5eCMQNQNvaQ7740V1X-Q&data=04%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C024432b580734c47d5fd08da193afd0a%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637850038395653915%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000&sdata=5GgW4mcQSa%2F7OeCuJNVuijJGG6wTRwDPlH27ZaMsY8Y%3D&reserved=0) was set up officially in June 2021 following a successful [Data Study Group](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FZhX5IuY0UnSKhrY2M7vI0g&data=04%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C024432b580734c47d5fd08da193afd0a%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637850038395653915%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000&sdata=%2FbfVrtcEmQBjdtgf%2BaeMg4IoZyAcpfI1kbuaQDlVXa4%3D&reserved=0) and a 12 week research project on lung cancer treatment. Our 'North Star' is **to enable the generation of insights to better understand patient and disease heterogeneity and its relevance to clinical outcomes at an unprecedented level of precision in order to improve clinical care.**

We will be covering multiple activities over the five years to work towards our North Star, as well as building strong connections and collaborations between the Alan Turing Institute, Roche and the wider community.

If you have anything you'd like featured in a future newsletter then please get in touch with Vicky Hellon, Community Manager for the partnership at <vhellon@turing.ac.uk>

If you would like to share this newsletter with relevant colleagues please direct them to sign-up [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FC0ad5R-KmNLdLsGrWK-T5g&data=04%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C024432b580734c47d5fd08da193afd0a%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637850038395653915%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000&sdata=qNBJDidUHe8reW8qG1GCm19yDCIQst9bGVNasDNsyMg%3D&reserved=0).

## Current Turing-Roche Strategic Partnership Updates


![](https://file-eu.clickdimensions.com/turingacuk-ap7zg/files/photo-1457530378978-8bac673b8062.jfif)


**New Knowledge Share Series**

**April 25 2022**

We are launching a [partnership knowledge share series](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FINCJ1dsPgvA4Kw_3kgAs1A&data=04%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C024432b580734c47d5fd08da193afd0a%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637850038395653915%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000&sdata=rzQHRqWnC%2FT5QocQmX5pS%2FmBaE89ETmE3Gxgw5GTdBc%3D&reserved=0)! Our aim is to bring together members of the Turing and Roche networks and beyond to share different academic and industry perspectives on areas related to patient/treatment heterogeneity and data science more generally.

Our first event is on April 25th and we'll be hearing from Dr Robin Mitra (Cardiff University) and Dr Chris Harbron (Roche) on the topic of Missing Data. You can register for the event [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FVecO5ARoGs3ejniwNWqbSQ&data=04%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C024432b580734c47d5fd08da193afd0a%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637850038395653915%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000&sdata=3KamiA4%2FH74%2BTWDFOAjckCbzpG0XGgMj2B5HHztaD2E%3D&reserved=0).

**Job: Senior Research Associate**

**Deadline 18 April 2022**

We are hiring a Senior Research Associate for the Turing-Roche partnership. The post is full-time for 3 years and will give the post holder experience working closely with both Turing and Roche to help shape direction of the partnership, as well as the freedom to develop their own area of aligned research under mentorship from senior leaders in both academia and industry.

More info at the job ad [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2F7S7bPv-FjISlWsSShfem0A&data=04%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C024432b580734c47d5fd08da193afd0a%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637850038395653915%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000&sdata=TXpOeiQKVtU9uzes13YjCj81G%2Bg1qF5czjnKIoVoeo4%3D&reserved=0)- please share widely!


## Current Opportunities at The Alan Turing Institute and Roche

![](https://file-eu.clickdimensions.com/turingacuk-ap7zg/files/group_study_working__0.jpg)


**Data Science and AI Educators' Programme at the Turing Institute**

**Running 16 May-15 August 2022**

**Deadline 24 April 2022**

The Turing Institute is launching a new 12 week Data Science and AI Educators' Programme. Taking a 'Train the Trainer' approach, the programme aims to equip educators and domain experts with pedagogical knowledge whilst developing participants professional skills, building their confidence as educators and embedding them in a nationwide network. The programme is welcoming a wide range of applicants (both internal and external to the Turing) such as teaching staff, researchers, industry practitioners and those who work in an educational setting. You can find out more info about the programme and how to apply [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%_%2FDLEEjyqEcDaH18gRn12-aQ&data=04%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C024432b580734c47d5fd08da193afd0a%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637850038395653915%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000&sdata=YtnQMkCZeP8NsTi0GUE%2B97RV7NXQzf9IdjkHHU%2BAXZw%3D&reserved=0).

**Roche Student Internship in Real World Data**

An opportunity for students to gain industry experience through an intership in the Real World Data Enabling Platform's data science team located in Basel, which consists of 60 data scientists with a diverse set of backgrounds (e.g epidemiology, statistics, medicine, biology, engineering, bioinformatics). The successful student will review current work and methodologies, plan a meta-analysis and present to a wide audience within Roche at the end of their internship. More info and how to apply [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FuQTgCw0ixlIjdvmmpiJQTA&data=04%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C024432b580734c47d5fd08da193afd0a%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637850038395653915%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000&sdata=%2BHIsby1r8ydosl3%2BdOVPXgr4m6rChOoznz9QyivXZKU%3D&reserved=0).

**Roche and UCL Global Business School launch new MBA Health Scholarship**

Roche have partnered with the UCL Global Business School for Health to launch a new fully-funded UCL MBA Health Scholarship which will cover the course fee, additional living expenses and travel to a low or middle-income country for two weeks to help find solutions to a health problem. The scholarship is open for applicants from a low-income background, BAME background or those who identify as female: aiming to increase opportunity in underrepresented groups who have historically been less likely to apply for MBA programmes. Find out more info and how to apply [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FPwfolL17rpcUpaVYPhMZmw&data=04%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C024432b580734c47d5fd08da193afd0a%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637850038395653915%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000&sdata=AgMnekiEtqpf4DBnuaXE3DlbDWwibf6fYIb1MGOmDPs%3D&reserved=0).

**Genomics England Research Summit**

**4 May 2022**

The Genomics England Research Summit is a one day event that explores the latest research and technology innovations from Genomics England, partners and complementary fields. There will be presentations and discussions across four main stages: rare diseases, cancer genomics, emerging technologies and policy. More info and registration [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FLUZkqcz7hKYUKFcr5U3O_w&data=04%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C024432b580734c47d5fd08da193afd0a%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637850038395653915%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000&sdata=eFfmKt7SpIFSQne3fxrBL8qtdsMJLMh4YIGRp512x4o%3D&reserved=0).

**Chan Zuckerberg Initiative Funding Call for Open Source Software**

**Deadline 19 April 2022**

The Chan Zuckerberg Initiative are inviting letters of intent to apply for funding for software projects that are essential to biomedical research. Grants will be for two years and can be used to fund a variety of eligible activities such as hiring staff, community engagement e.g hackathons or operational needs e.g cloud computing. **Call for Abstracts at ISMB 2022**

**Deadline 21 April 2022**

ISMB 2022 is taking place July 10-14 as a hybrid meeting and is inviting abstracts for research that is topical to bioinformatics and computational biology. Of particular interest may be the Machine Learning in Computational Systems Biology Track which is inviting submissions and will be hosting a discussion panel on 'Reproducibility and Transparency in ML: training the next generation'. Find out more [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FzxwhI0NG2m2TJRBtf1ifDg&data=04%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C024432b580734c47d5fd08da193afd0a%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637850038395653915%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000&sdata=Gz0PZNhAqJhsX1gBAUteCRxLQEuThv1X8pdMgDIJz5U%3D&reserved=0).
